Sentencas: Transition metal oxides (FeO1.5 and COO) were added to Gd-doped ceria (Gd0.1Ce0.9O2-delta, GDC) powder for preparing the thin-film electrolyte used in the anode-supported intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC).
Titulo: Effects of transition metal oxides on the densification of thin-film GDC electrolyte and on the performance of intermediate-temperature SOFC

Sentencas: NiO-GDC anode substrate in a weight ratio of 65:35 was fabricated by the tape-casting method.
Titulo: Effects of transition metal oxides on the densification of thin-film GDC electrolyte and on the performance of intermediate-temperature SOFC

Sentencas: Thin-film electrolyte was fabricated on the presintered anode substrate by screen-printing method and then co-sintered to form the electrolyte/anode bilayer.
Titulo: Effects of transition metal oxides on the densification of thin-film GDC electrolyte and on the performance of intermediate-temperature SOFC

Sentencas: The cathode, which is made of La0.6Sr0.4Fe0.8Co0.2O3 and GDC (LSCF-GDC) in a weight ratio of 50:50, was screen-printed on the thus-prepared electrolyte surface and sintered to form a complete single cell.
Titulo: Effects of transition metal oxides on the densification of thin-film GDC electrolyte and on the performance of intermediate-temperature SOFC

Sentencas: The effects of transition metal oxides on the densification of thin-film GDC electrolyte and on the performance of intermediate-temperature SOFC were studied.
Titulo: Effects of transition metal oxides on the densification of thin-film GDC electrolyte and on the performance of intermediate-temperature SOFC

Sentencas: Results showed that the densification temperature of thin-film GDC electrolyte could not be further reduced by modifying it with transition metal oxides (FeO1.5 and CoO) as sintering aids.
Titulo: Effects of transition metal oxides on the densification of thin-film GDC electrolyte and on the performance of intermediate-temperature SOFC

Sentencas: Both the addition of Fe and Co to GDC enhanced the p-type conductivity of the electrolyte resulting in decreased ohmic resistance.
Titulo: Effects of transition metal oxides on the densification of thin-film GDC electrolyte and on the performance of intermediate-temperature SOFC

Sentencas: However, they played different effects on the polarization behavior of the cells.
Titulo: Effects of transition metal oxides on the densification of thin-film GDC electrolyte and on the performance of intermediate-temperature SOFC

Sentencas: Fe-loading decreased the single cell polarization resistance, thus greatly enhancing the charge-transfer process below 600 degrees C.
Titulo: Effects of transition metal oxides on the densification of thin-film GDC electrolyte and on the performance of intermediate-temperature SOFC

Sentencas: At 500 degrees C, the chargetransfer resistance of the single cell with Fe-loaded GDC electrolyte is only 78% of that of the cell with pure GDC electrolyte.
Titulo: Effects of transition metal oxides on the densification of thin-film GDC electrolyte and on the performance of intermediate-temperature SOFC

Sentencas: Conversely, Co-loading inhibited the charge-transfer process in the whole testing temperature range.
Titulo: Effects of transition metal oxides on the densification of thin-film GDC electrolyte and on the performance of intermediate-temperature SOFC

Sentencas: Thus, it can be concluded that Fe-loaded GDC electrolyte is a promising electrolyte material for intermediate- and low-temperature SOFC.
Titulo: Effects of transition metal oxides on the densification of thin-film GDC electrolyte and on the performance of intermediate-temperature SOFC
